    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="512"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>What has recently occurred regarding Kongo cession? Upon recent reports of
                    continued oppression of natives of the Kongo, this Government is much indisposed
                    to delay urgent representations in the sense of my letter to Ambassador Reid
                    dated November 4,<note n="2" xml:id="d512fn2">See <ref
                            target="frus1907p2#pg_812">Foreign Relations, 1907, p. 812</ref>.</note>
                    transmitted to you November 6. Cable report promptly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
